	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I have connected my "new" NES to my 40" LCD using the RF-cable. However the image appears "Jumpy" (bounces up and down, perhaps +10 pixels or so). After resetting the unit a few times the problem usually goes away.
<br />Anyone knows what could be causing this?
<br />My TV? Could dirty cartridges result in a jumpy image? The connector in the unit itself is brand new..

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


